135	  \uses{def:Modules_tensorObj, thm:Modules_MonoidalCategory}
136	  \leanok
137	  This is the standard assertion that the inverse-image functor on $\mathcal O$-modules is monoidal. Mathlib provides $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f$ as a functor on quasi-coherent $\mathcal O$-modules and has the corresponding statement on the presheaf side, but \texttt{b80f227} does not register a $\mathrm{Functor.Monoidal}\,(\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f)$ instance. The proof proceeds by the tensor-hom adjunction together with the fact that the pull-back of the structure-sheaf-unit map is again a unit map; see Stacks~\texttt{01AC} and \S5 of Hartshorne~II for the affine-local picture. A future Mathlib refresh that lands $(\mathrm{SheafOfModules.pullback}\,\_).\mathrm{Monoidal}$ collapses this obligation to the canonical $\mathrm{MonoidalCategoryStruct.tensorObj}$-comparison.
