152	\begin{proof}
153	  \uses{thm:Modules_MonoidalCategory}
154	  \leanok
155	  Unit-preservation is the natural sister of Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj}: it is the $\varepsilon$-iso of the (missing) $\mathrm{Functor.Monoidal}\,(\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f)$ instance, paired with the $\mu$-iso of Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj}. Mathematically: the pull-back of the structure sheaf $\mathcal O_Y$ along $f \colon X \to Y$ is the structure sheaf $\mathcal O_X$ (Stacks~\texttt{01AC}; this is part of the very definition of inverse-image of sheaves of modules, namely that $f^* \mathcal O_Y = \mathcal O_X$ as the canonical $\mathcal O_X$-module structure on the inverse-image presheaf coincides with the structure-sheaf identity). A future Mathlib refresh landing $(\mathrm{SheafOfModules.pullback}\,\_).\mathrm{Monoidal}$ collapses this obligation to the canonical $\mathrm{Monoidal.}\varepsilon\mathrm{Iso}$ structure field.
156	\end{proof}
