160	The Picard group $\Pic(X)$ is the underlying \emph{set} (modulo isomorphism) of the Picard \emph{scheme} $\Pic_{C/k}$ in the curve case; the scheme structure adds a $k$-scheme of finite type representing the relative Picard functor $S \mapsto \Pic(C \times_k S) / \Pic(S)$.
